title._content: [Portrait of Imogene Coca, Café Society (Downtown)(?), New York, N.Y., ca. June 1947] (LOC)

description._content: Gottlieb, William P., 1917-, photographer. [Portrait of Imogene Coca, Café Society (Downtown)(?), New York, N.Y., ca. June 1947] 1 negative : b&w ; 2 1/4 x 2 1/4 in. Caption from Down Beat: This versatile Café Society Downtown lass is Imogene Coca. Shown here in her Down Beat sweater, Miss Coca challenges Jane Russell and Betty George to do as well, though she admits these are phonies made out of coconuts. Notes: Gottlieb Collection Assignment No. 077 Reference print available in Music Division, Library of Congress. Purchase William P. Gottlieb Forms part of: William P. Gottlieb Collection (Library of Congress). In: "Café's Coca," Down Beat, v. 14, no. 12 (June 4, 1947), p. 1. Subjects: Coca, Imogene Women comedians--1940-1950. Format: Portrait photographs--1940-1950. Film negatives--1940-1950.
